      • setNoConnectionReaction

        public void setNoConnectionReaction(RequestParcel.NoConnectionReaction noConnectionReaction)
        Set parcel's reaction to "not connected to network" situation. Parcel may be queued or rejected in this case. Parcels related to continuous background operations may be enqueued or resent. Interactive operations should be rejected to notify user that there is no connection available.
        Parameters:
        noConnectionReaction - Reject/Enqueus/Resend values
